4229
4230/* Return a positive integer if X should sort after Y. The value
4231 returned is 1 if and only if X and Y are both regs. */
4232
4233static int
4234simplify_plus_minus_op_data_cmp (rtx x, rtx y)
4235{
4236 int result;
4237
4238 result = (commutative_operand_precedence (y)
4239 - commutative_operand_precedence (x));
4240 if (result)
4241 return result + result;
4242
4243 /* Group together equal REGs to do more simplification. */
4244 if (REG_P (x) && REG_P (y))
4245 return REGNO (x) > REGNO (y);
4246
4247 return 0;
4248}
4249
4250/* Simplify and canonicalize a PLUS or MINUS, at least one of whose
4251 operands may be another PLUS or MINUS.
4252
4253 Rather than test for specific case, we do this by a brute-force method
4254 and do all possible simplifications until no more changes occur. Then
4255 we rebuild the operation.
4256
4257 May return NULL_RTX when no changes were made. */
4258
4259static rtx
4260simplify_plus_minus (enum rtx_code code, machine_mode mode, rtx op0,
4261 rtx op1)
4262{
4263 struct simplify_plus_minus_op_data
4264 {
4265 rtx op;
4266 short neg;
4267 } ops[16];
4268 rtx result, tem;
4269 int n_ops = 2;
4270 int changed, n_constants, canonicalized = 0;
4271 int i, j;
4272
4273 memset (ops, 0, sizeof ops);
4274
4275 /* Set up the two operands and then expand them until nothing has been
4276 changed. If we run out of room in our array, give up; this should
4277 almost never happen. */
4278
4279 ops[0].op = op0;
4280 ops[0].neg = 0;
4281 ops[1].op = op1;
4282 ops[1].neg = (code == MINUS);
4283
4284 do
4285 {
4286 changed = 0;
4287 n_constants = 0;
4288
4289 for (i = 0; i < n_ops; i++)
4290 {
4291 rtx this_op = ops[i].op;
4292 int this_neg = ops[i].neg;
4293 enum rtx_code this_code = GET_CODE (this_op);
4294
4295 switch (this_code)
4296 {
4297 case PLUS:
4298 case MINUS:
4299 if (n_ops == ARRAY_SIZE (ops))
4300 return NULL_RTX;
4301
4302 ops[n_ops].op = XEXP (this_op, 1);
4303 ops[n_ops].neg = (this_code == MINUS) ^ this_neg;
4304 n_ops++;
4305
4306 ops[i].op = XEXP (this_op, 0);
4307 changed = 1;
4308 /* If this operand was negated then we will potentially
4309 canonicalize the expression. Similarly if we don't
4310 place the operands adjacent we're re-ordering the
4311 expression and thus might be performing a
4312 canonicalization. Ignore register re-ordering.
4313 ??? It might be better to shuffle the ops array here,
4314 but then (plus (plus (A, B), plus (C, D))) wouldn't
4315 be seen as non-canonical. */
4316 if (this_neg
4317 || (i != n_ops - 2
4318 && !(REG_P (ops[i].op) && REG_P (ops[n_ops - 1].op))))
4319 canonicalized = 1;
4320 break;
4321
4322 case NEG:
4323 ops[i].op = XEXP (this_op, 0);
4324 ops[i].neg = ! this_neg;
4325 changed = 1;
4326 canonicalized = 1;
4327 break;
4328
4329 case CONST:
4330 if (n_ops != ARRAY_SIZE (ops)
4331 && GET_CODE (XEXP (this_op, 0)) == PLUS
4332 && CONSTANT_P (XEXP (XEXP (this_op, 0), 0))
4333 && CONSTANT_P (XEXP (XEXP (this_op, 0), 1)))
4334 {
4335 ops[i].op = XEXP (XEXP (this_op, 0), 0);
4336 ops[n_ops].op = XEXP (XEXP (this_op, 0), 1);
4337 ops[n_ops].neg = this_neg;
4338 n_ops++;
4339 changed = 1;
4340 canonicalized = 1;
4341 }
4342 break;
4343
4344 case NOT:
4345 /* ~a -> (-a - 1) */
4346 if (n_ops != ARRAY_SIZE (ops))
4347 {
4348 ops[n_ops].op = CONSTM1_RTX (mode);
4349 ops[n_ops++].neg = this_neg;
4350 ops[i].op = XEXP (this_op, 0);
4351 ops[i].neg = !this_neg;
4352 changed = 1;
4353 canonicalized = 1;
4354 }
4355 break;
4356
4357 case CONST_INT:
4358 n_constants++;
4359 if (this_neg)
4360 {
4361 ops[i].op = neg_const_int (mode, this_op);
4362 ops[i].neg = 0;
4363 changed = 1;
4364 canonicalized = 1;
4365 }
4366 break;
4367
4368 default:
4369 break;
4370 }
4371 }
4372 }
4373 while (changed);
4374
4375 if (n_constants > 1)
4376 canonicalized = 1;
4377
4378 gcc_assert (n_ops >= 2);
4379
4380 /* If we only have two operands, we can avoid the loops. */
4381 if (n_ops == 2)
4382 {
4383 enum rtx_code code = ops[0].neg || ops[1].neg ? MINUS : PLUS;
4384 rtx lhs, rhs;
4385
4386 /* Get the two operands. Be careful with the order, especially for
4387 the cases where code == MINUS. */
4388 if (ops[0].neg && ops[1].neg)
4389 {
4390 lhs = gen_rtx_NEG (mode, ops[0].op);
4391 rhs = ops[1].op;
4392 }
4393 else if (ops[0].neg)
4394 {
4395 lhs = ops[1].op;
4396 rhs = ops[0].op;
4397 }
4398 else
4399 {
4400 lhs = ops[0].op;
4401 rhs = ops[1].op;
4402 }
4403
4404 return simplify_const_binary_operation (code, mode, lhs, rhs);
4405 }
4406
4407 /* Now simplify each pair of operands until nothing changes. */
4408 while (1)
4409 {
4410 /* Insertion sort is good enough for a small array. */
4411 for (i = 1; i < n_ops; i++)
4412 {
4413 struct simplify_plus_minus_op_data save;
4414 int cmp;
4415
4416 j = i - 1;
4417 cmp = simplify_plus_minus_op_data_cmp (ops[j].op, ops[i].op);
4418 if (cmp <= 0)
4419 continue;
4420 /* Just swapping registers doesn't count as canonicalization. */
4421 if (cmp != 1)
4422 canonicalized = 1;
4423
4424 save = ops[i];
4425 do
4426 ops[j + 1] = ops[j];
4427 while (j--
4428 && simplify_plus_minus_op_data_cmp (ops[j].op, save.op) > 0);
4429 ops[j + 1] = save;
4430 }
4431
4432 changed = 0;
4433 for (i = n_ops - 1; i > 0; i--)
4434 for (j = i - 1; j >= 0; j--)
4435 {
4436 rtx lhs = ops[j].op, rhs = ops[i].op;
4437 int lneg = ops[j].neg, rneg = ops[i].neg;
4438
4439 if (lhs != 0 && rhs != 0)
4440 {
4441 enum rtx_code ncode = PLUS;
4442
4443 if (lneg != rneg)
4444 {
4445 ncode = MINUS;
4446 if (lneg)
4447 std::swap (lhs, rhs);
4448 }
4449 else if (swap_commutative_operands_p (lhs, rhs))
4450 std::swap (lhs, rhs);
4451
4452 if ((GET_CODE (lhs) == CONST || CONST_INT_P (lhs))
4453 && (GET_CODE (rhs) == CONST || CONST_INT_P (rhs)))
4454 {
4455 rtx tem_lhs, tem_rhs;
4456
4457 tem_lhs = GET_CODE (lhs) == CONST ? XEXP (lhs, 0) : lhs;
4458 tem_rhs = GET_CODE (rhs) == CONST ? XEXP (rhs, 0) : rhs;
4459 tem = simplify_binary_operation (ncode, mode, tem_lhs,
4460 tem_rhs);
4461
4462 if (tem && !CONSTANT_P (tem))
4463 tem = gen_rtx_CONST (GET_MODE (tem), tem);
4464 }
4465 else
4466 tem = simplify_binary_operation (ncode, mode, lhs, rhs);
4467
4468 if (tem)
4469 {
4470 /* Reject "simplifications" that just wrap the two
4471 arguments in a CONST. Failure to do so can result
4472 in infinite recursion with simplify_binary_operation
4473 when it calls us to simplify CONST operations.
4474 Also, if we find such a simplification, don't try
4475 any more combinations with this rhs: We must have
4476 something like symbol+offset, ie. one of the
4477 trivial CONST expressions we handle later. */
4478 if (GET_CODE (tem) == CONST
4479 && GET_CODE (XEXP (tem, 0)) == ncode
4480 && XEXP (XEXP (tem, 0), 0) == lhs
4481 && XEXP (XEXP (tem, 0), 1) == rhs)
4482 break;
4483 lneg &= rneg;
4484 if (GET_CODE (tem) == NEG)
4485 tem = XEXP (tem, 0), lneg = !lneg;
4486 if (CONST_INT_P (tem) && lneg)
4487 tem = neg_const_int (mode, tem), lneg = 0;
4488
4489 ops[i].op = tem;
4490 ops[i].neg = lneg;
4491 ops[j].op = NULL_RTX;
4492 changed = 1;
4493 canonicalized = 1;
4494 }
4495 }
4496 }
4497
4498 if (!changed)
4499 break;
4500
4501 /* Pack all the operands to the lower-numbered entries. */
4502 for (i = 0, j = 0; j < n_ops; j++)
4503 if (ops[j].op)
4504 {
4505 ops[i] = ops[j];
4506 i++;
4507 }
4508 n_ops = i;
4509 }
4510
4511 /* If nothing changed, check that rematerialization of rtl instructions
4512 is still required. */
4513 if (!canonicalized)
4514 {
4515 /* Perform rematerialization if only all operands are registers and
4516 all operations are PLUS. */
4517 /* ??? Also disallow (non-global, non-frame) fixed registers to work
4518 around rs6000 and how it uses the CA register. See PR67145. */
4519 for (i = 0; i < n_ops; i++)
4520 if (ops[i].neg
4521 || !REG_P (ops[i].op)
4522 || (REGNO (ops[i].op) < FIRST_PSEUDO_REGISTER
4523 && fixed_regs[REGNO (ops[i].op)]
4524 && !global_regs[REGNO (ops[i].op)]
4525 && ops[i].op != frame_pointer_rtx
4526 && ops[i].op != arg_pointer_rtx
4527 && ops[i].op != stack_pointer_rtx))
4528 return NULL_RTX;
4529 goto gen_result;
4530 }
4531
4532 /* Create (minus -C X) instead of (neg (const (plus X C))). */
4533 if (n_ops == 2
4534 && CONST_INT_P (ops[1].op)
4535 && CONSTANT_P (ops[0].op)
4536 && ops[0].neg)
4537 return gen_rtx_fmt_ee (MINUS, mode, ops[1].op, ops[0].op);
4538
4539 /* We suppressed creation of trivial CONST expressions in the
4540 combination loop to avoid recursion. Create one manually now.
4541 The combination loop should have ensured that there is exactly
4542 one CONST_INT, and the sort will have ensured that it is last
4543 in the array and that any other constant will be next-to-last. */
4544
4545 if (n_ops > 1
4546 && CONST_INT_P (ops[n_ops - 1].op)
4547 && CONSTANT_P (ops[n_ops - 2].op))
4548 {
4549 rtx value = ops[n_ops - 1].op;
4550 if (ops[n_ops - 1].neg ^ ops[n_ops - 2].neg)
4551 value = neg_const_int (mode, value);
4552 if (CONST_INT_P (value))
4553 {
4554 ops[n_ops - 2].op = plus_constant (mode, ops[n_ops - 2].op,
4555 INTVAL (value));
4556 n_ops--;
4557 }
4558 }
4559
4560 /* Put a non-negated operand first, if possible. */
4561
4562 for (i = 0; i < n_ops && ops[i].neg; i++)
4563 continue;
4564 if (i == n_ops)
4565 ops[0].op = gen_rtx_NEG (mode, ops[0].op);
4566 else if (i != 0)
4567 {
4568 tem = ops[0].op;
4569 ops[0] = ops[i];
4570 ops[i].op = tem;
4571 ops[i].neg = 1;
4572 }
4573
4574 /* Now make the result by performing the requested operations. */
4575 gen_result:
4576 result = ops[0].op;
4577 for (i = 1; i < n_ops; i++)
4578 result = gen_rtx_fmt_ee (ops[i].neg ? MINUS : PLUS,
4579 mode, result, ops[i].op);
4580
4581 return result;
4582}
4583
4584/* Check whether an operand is suitable for calling simplify_plus_minus. */
4585static bool
4586plus_minus_operand_p (const_rtx x)
4587{
4588 return GET_CODE (x) == PLUS
4589 || GET_CODE (x) == MINUS
4590 || (GET_CODE (x) == CONST
4591 && GET_CODE (XEXP (x, 0)) == PLUS
4592 && CONSTANT_P (XEXP (XEXP (x, 0), 0))
4593 && CONSTANT_P (XEXP (XEXP (x, 0), 1)));
4594}
4595
4596/* Like simplify_binary_operation except used for relational operators.
4597 MODE is the mode of the result. If MODE is VOIDmode, both operands must
4598 not also be VOIDmode.
4599
4600 CMP_MODE specifies in which mode the comparison is done in, so it is
4601 the mode of the operands. If CMP_MODE is VOIDmode, it is taken from
4602 the operands or, if both are VOIDmode, the operands are compared in
4603 "infinite precision". */
4604rtx
4605simplify_relational_operation (enum rtx_code code, machine_mode mode,
4606 machine_mode cmp_mode, rtx op0, rtx op1)
4607{
4608 rtx tem, trueop0, trueop1;
4609
4610 if (cmp_mode == VOIDmode)
4611 cmp_mode = GET_MODE (op0);
4612 if (cmp_mode == VOIDmode)
4613 cmp_mode = GET_MODE (op1);
4614
4615 tem = simplify_const_relational_operation (code, cmp_mode, op0, op1);
4616 if (tem)
4617 {
4618 if (SCALAR_FLOAT_MODE_P (mode))
4619 {
4620 if (tem == const0_rtx)
4621 return CONST0_RTX (mode);
4622#ifdef FLOAT_STORE_FLAG_VALUE
4623 {
4624 REAL_VALUE_TYPE val;
4625 val = FLOAT_STORE_FLAG_VALUE (mode);
4626 return const_double_from_real_value (val, mode);
4627 }
4628#else
4629 return NULL_RTX;
4630#endif
4631 }
4632 if (VECTOR_MODE_P (mode))
4633 {
4634 if (tem == const0_rtx)
4635 return CONST0_RTX (mode);
4636#ifdef VECTOR_STORE_FLAG_VALUE
4637 {
4638 int i, units;
4639 rtvec v;
4640
4641 rtx val = VECTOR_STORE_FLAG_VALUE (mode);
4642 if (val == NULL_RTX)
4643 return NULL_RTX;
4644 if (val == const1_rtx)
4645 return CONST1_RTX (mode);
4646
4647 units = GET_MODE_NUNITS (mode);
4648 v = rtvec_alloc (units);
4649 for (i = 0; i < units; i++)
4650 RTVEC_ELT (v, i) = val;
4651 return gen_rtx_raw_CONST_VECTOR (mode, v);
4652 }
4653#else
4654 return NULL_RTX;
4655#endif
4656 }
4657
4658 return tem;
4659 }
4660
4661 /* For the following tests, ensure const0_rtx is op1. */
4662 if (swap_commutative_operands_p (op0, op1)
4663 || (op0 == const0_rtx && op1 != const0_rtx))
4664 std::swap (op0, op1), code = swap_condition (code);
4665
4666 /* If op0 is a compare, extract the comparison arguments from it. */
4667 if (GET_CODE (op0) == COMPARE && op1 == const0_rtx)
4668 return simplify_gen_relational (code, mode, VOIDmode,
4669 XEXP (op0, 0), XEXP (op0, 1));
4670
4671 if (GET_MODE_CLASS (cmp_mode) == MODE_CC
4672 || CC0_P (op0))
4673 return NULL_RTX;
4674
4675 trueop0 = avoid_constant_pool_reference (op0);
4676 trueop1 = avoid_constant_pool_reference (op1);
4677 return simplify_relational_operation_1 (code, mode, cmp_mode,
4678 trueop0, trueop1);
4679}
4680
4681/* This part of simplify_relational_operation is only used when CMP_MODE
4682 is not in class MODE_CC (i.e. it is a real comparison).
4683
4684 MODE is the mode of the result, while CMP_MODE specifies in which
4685 mode the comparison is done in, so it is the mode of the operands. */
4686
4687static rtx
4688simplify_relational_operation_1 (enum rtx_code code, machine_mode mode,
4689 machine_mode cmp_mode, rtx op0, rtx op1)
4690{
4691 enum rtx_code op0code = GET_CODE (op0);
4692
4693 if (op1 == const0_rtx && COMPARISON_P (op0))
4694 {
4695 /* If op0 is a comparison, extract the comparison arguments
4696 from it. */
4697 if (code == NE)
4698 {
4699 if (GET_MODE (op0) == mode)
4700 return simplify_rtx (op0);
4701 else
4702 return simplify_gen_relational (GET_CODE (op0), mode, VOIDmode,
4703 XEXP (op0, 0), XEXP (op0, 1));
4704 }
4705 else if (code == EQ)
4706 {
4707 enum rtx_code new_code = reversed_comparison_code (op0, NULL);
4708 if (new_code != UNKNOWN)
4709 return simplify_gen_relational (new_code, mode, VOIDmode,
4710 XEXP (op0, 0), XEXP (op0, 1));
4711 }
4712 }
4713
4714 /* (LTU/GEU (PLUS a C) C), where C is constant, can be simplified to
4715 (GEU/LTU a -C). Likewise for (LTU/GEU (PLUS a C) a). */
4716 if ((code == LTU || code == GEU)
4717 && GET_CODE (op0) == PLUS
4718 && CONST_INT_P (XEXP (op0, 1))
4719 && (rtx_equal_p (op1, XEXP (op0, 0))
4720 || rtx_equal_p (op1, XEXP (op0, 1)))
4721 /* (LTU/GEU (PLUS a 0) 0) is not the same as (GEU/LTU a 0). */
4722 && XEXP (op0, 1) != const0_rtx)
4723 {
4724 rtx new_cmp
4725 = simplify_gen_unary (NEG, cmp_mode, XEXP (op0, 1), cmp_mode);
4726 return simplify_gen_relational ((code == LTU ? GEU : LTU), mode,
4727 cmp_mode, XEXP (op0, 0), new_cmp);
4728 }
4729
4730 /* (GTU (PLUS a C) (C - 1)) where C is a non-zero constant can be
4731 transformed into (LTU a -C). */
4732 if (code == GTU && GET_CODE (op0) == PLUS && CONST_INT_P (op1)
4733 && CONST_INT_P (XEXP (op0, 1))
4734 && (UINTVAL (op1) == UINTVAL (XEXP (op0, 1)) - 1)
4735 && XEXP (op0, 1) != const0_rtx)
4736 {
4737 rtx new_cmp
4738 = simplify_gen_unary (NEG, cmp_mode, XEXP (op0, 1), cmp_mode);
4739 return simplify_gen_relational (LTU, mode, cmp_mode,
4740 XEXP (op0, 0), new_cmp);
4741 }
4742
4743 /* Canonicalize (LTU/GEU (PLUS a b) b) as (LTU/GEU (PLUS a b) a). */
4744 if ((code == LTU || code == GEU)
4745 && GET_CODE (op0) == PLUS
4746 && rtx_equal_p (op1, XEXP (op0, 1))
4747 /* Don't recurse "infinitely" for (LTU/GEU (PLUS b b) b). */
4748 && !rtx_equal_p (op1, XEXP (op0, 0)))
4749 return simplify_gen_relational (code, mode, cmp_mode, op0,
4750 copy_rtx (XEXP (op0, 0)));
4751
4752 if (op1 == const0_rtx)
4753 {
4754 /* Canonicalize (GTU x 0) as (NE x 0). */
4755 if (code == GTU)
4756 return simplify_gen_relational (NE, mode, cmp_mode, op0, op1);
4757 /* Canonicalize (LEU x 0) as (EQ x 0). */
4758 if (code == LEU)
4759 return simplify_gen_relational (EQ, mode, cmp_mode, op0, op1);
4760 }
4761 else if (op1 == const1_rtx)
4762 {
4763 switch (code)
4764 {
4765 case GE:
4766 /* Canonicalize (GE x 1) as (GT x 0). */
4767 return simplify_gen_relational (GT, mode, cmp_mode,
4768 op0, const0_rtx);
4769 case GEU:
4770 /* Canonicalize (GEU x 1) as (NE x 0). */
4771 return simplify_gen_relational (NE, mode, cmp_mode,
4772 op0, const0_rtx);
4773 case LT:
4774 /* Canonicalize (LT x 1) as (LE x 0). */
4775 return simplify_gen_relational (LE, mode, cmp_mode,
4776 op0, const0_rtx);
4777 case LTU:
4778 /* Canonicalize (LTU x 1) as (EQ x 0). */
4779 return simplify_gen_relational (EQ, mode, cmp_mode,
4780 op0, const0_rtx);
4781 default:
4782 break;
4783 }
4784 }
4785 else if (op1 == constm1_rtx)
4786 {
4787 /* Canonicalize (LE x -1) as (LT x 0). */
4788 if (code == LE)
4789 return simplify_gen_relational (LT, mode, cmp_mode, op0, const0_rtx);
4790 /* Canonicalize (GT x -1) as (GE x 0). */
4791 if (code == GT)
4792 return simplify_gen_relational (GE, mode, cmp_mode, op0, const0_rtx);
4793 }
4794
4795 /* (eq/ne (plus x cst1) cst2) simplifies to (eq/ne x (cst2 - cst1)) */
4796 if ((code == EQ || code == NE)
4797 && (op0code == PLUS || op0code == MINUS)
4798 && CONSTANT_P (op1)
4799 && CONSTANT_P (XEXP (op0, 1))
4800 && (INTEGRAL_MODE_P (cmp_mode) || flag_unsafe_math_optimizations))
4801 {
4802 rtx x = XEXP (op0, 0);
4803 rtx c = XEXP (op0, 1);
4804 enum rtx_code invcode = op0code == PLUS ? MINUS : PLUS;
4805 rtx tem = simplify_gen_binary (invcode, cmp_mode, op1, c);
4806
4807 /* Detect an infinite recursive condition, where we oscillate at this
4808 simplification case between:
4809 A + B == C <---> C - B == A,
4810 where A, B, and C are all constants with non-simplifiable expressions,
4811 usually SYMBOL_REFs. */
4812 if (GET_CODE (tem) == invcode
4813 && CONSTANT_P (x)
4814 && rtx_equal_p (c, XEXP (tem, 1)))
4815 return NULL_RTX;
4816
4817 return simplify_gen_relational (code, mode, cmp_mode, x, tem);
4818 }
4819
4820 /* (ne:SI (zero_extract:SI FOO (const_int 1) BAR) (const_int 0))) is
4821 the same as (zero_extract:SI FOO (const_int 1) BAR). */
4822 if (code == NE
4823 && op1 == const0_rtx
4824 && GET_MODE_CLASS (mode) == MODE_INT
4825 && cmp_mode != VOIDmode
4826 /* ??? Work-around BImode bugs in the ia64 backend. */
4827 && mode != BImode
4828 && cmp_mode != BImode
4829 && nonzero_bits (op0, cmp_mode) == 1
4830 && STORE_FLAG_VALUE == 1)
4831 return GET_MODE_SIZE (mode) > GET_MODE_SIZE (cmp_mode)
4832 ? simplify_gen_unary (ZERO_EXTEND, mode, op0, cmp_mode)
4833 : lowpart_subreg (mode, op0, cmp_mode);
4834
4835 /* (eq/ne (xor x y) 0) simplifies to (eq/ne x y). */
4836 if ((code == EQ || code == NE)
4837 && op1 == const0_rtx
4838 && op0code == XOR)
4839 return simplify_gen_relational (code, mode, cmp_mode,
4840 XEXP (op0, 0), XEXP (op0, 1));
4841
4842 /* (eq/ne (xor x y) x) simplifies to (eq/ne y 0). */
4843 if ((code == EQ || code == NE)
4844 && op0code == XOR
4845 && rtx_equal_p (XEXP (op0, 0), op1)
4846 && !side_effects_p (XEXP (op0, 0)))
4847 return simplify_gen_relational (code, mode, cmp_mode, XEXP (op0, 1),
4848 CONST0_RTX (mode));
4849
4850 /* Likewise (eq/ne (xor x y) y) simplifies to (eq/ne x 0). */
4851 if ((code == EQ || code == NE)
4852 && op0code == XOR
4853 && rtx_equal_p (XEXP (op0, 1), op1)
4854 && !side_effects_p (XEXP (op0, 1)))
4855 return simplify_gen_relational (code, mode, cmp_mode, XEXP (op0, 0),
4856 CONST0_RTX (mode));
4857
4858 /* (eq/ne (xor x C1) C2) simplifies to (eq/ne x (C1^C2)). */
4859 if ((code == EQ || code == NE)
4860 && op0code == XOR
4861 && CONST_SCALAR_INT_P (op1)
4862 && CONST_SCALAR_INT_P (XEXP (op0, 1)))
4863 return simplify_gen_relational (code, mode, cmp_mode, XEXP (op0, 0),
4864 simplify_gen_binary (XOR, cmp_mode,
4865 XEXP (op0, 1), op1));
4866
4867 /* (eq/ne (and x y) x) simplifies to (eq/ne (and (not y) x) 0), which
4868 can be implemented with a BICS instruction on some targets, or
4869 constant-folded if y is a constant. */
4870 if ((code == EQ || code == NE)
4871 && op0code == AND
4872 && rtx_equal_p (XEXP (op0, 0), op1)
4873 && !side_effects_p (op1)
4874 && op1 != CONST0_RTX (cmp_mode))
4875 {
4876 rtx not_y = simplify_gen_unary (NOT, cmp_mode, XEXP (op0, 1), cmp_mode);
4877 rtx lhs = simplify_gen_binary (AND, cmp_mode, not_y, XEXP (op0, 0));
4878
4879 return simplify_gen_relational (code, mode, cmp_mode, lhs,
4880 CONST0_RTX (cmp_mode));
4881 }
4882
4883 /* Likewise for (eq/ne (and x y) y). */
4884 if ((code == EQ || code == NE)
4885 && op0code == AND
4886 && rtx_equal_p (XEXP (op0, 1), op1)
4887 && !side_effects_p (op1)
4888 && op1 != CONST0_RTX (cmp_mode))
4889 {
4890 rtx not_x = simplify_gen_unary (NOT, cmp_mode, XEXP (op0, 0), cmp_mode);
4891 rtx lhs = simplify_gen_binary (AND, cmp_mode, not_x, XEXP (op0, 1));
4892
4893 return simplify_gen_relational (code, mode, cmp_mode, lhs,
4894 CONST0_RTX (cmp_mode));
4895 }
4896
4897 /* (eq/ne (bswap x) C1) simplifies to (eq/ne x C2) with C2 swapped. */
4898 if ((code == EQ || code == NE)
4899 && GET_CODE (op0) == BSWAP
4900 && CONST_SCALAR_INT_P (op1))
4901 return simplify_gen_relational (code, mode, cmp_mode, XEXP (op0, 0),
4902 simplify_gen_unary (BSWAP, cmp_mode,
4903 op1, cmp_mode));
4904
4905 /* (eq/ne (bswap x) (bswap y)) simplifies to (eq/ne x y). */
4906 if ((code == EQ || code == NE)
4907 && GET_CODE (op0) == BSWAP
4908 && GET_CODE (op1) == BSWAP)
4909 return simplify_gen_relational (code, mode, cmp_mode,
4910 XEXP (op0, 0), XEXP (op1, 0));
4911
4912 if (op0code == POPCOUNT && op1 == const0_rtx)
4913 switch (code)
4914 {
4915 case EQ:
4916 case LE:
4917 case LEU:
4918 /* (eq (popcount x) (const_int 0)) -> (eq x (const_int 0)). */
4919 return simplify_gen_relational (EQ, mode, GET_MODE (XEXP (op0, 0)),
4920 XEXP (op0, 0), const0_rtx);
4921
4922 case NE:
4923 case GT:
4924 case GTU:
4925 /* (ne (popcount x) (const_int 0)) -> (ne x (const_int 0)). */
4926 return simplify_gen_relational (NE, mode, GET_MODE (XEXP (op0, 0)),
4927 XEXP (op0, 0), const0_rtx);
4928
4929 default:
4930 break;
4931 }
4932
4933 return NULL_RTX;
4934}
4935
4936enum
4937{
4938 CMP_EQ = 1,
4939 CMP_LT = 2,
4940 CMP_GT = 4,
4941 CMP_LTU = 8,
4942 CMP_GTU = 16
4943};
4944
4945
4946/* Convert the known results for EQ, LT, GT, LTU, GTU contained in
4947 KNOWN_RESULT to a CONST_INT, based on the requested comparison CODE
4948 For KNOWN_RESULT to make sense it should be either CMP_EQ, or the
4949 logical OR of one of (CMP_LT, CMP_GT) and one of (CMP_LTU, CMP_GTU).
4950 For floating-point comparisons, assume that the operands were ordered. */
4951
4952static rtx
4953comparison_result (enum rtx_code code, int known_results)
4954{
4955 switch (code)
4956 {
4957 case EQ:
4958 case UNEQ:
4959 return (known_results & CMP_EQ) ? const_true_rtx : const0_rtx;
4960 case NE:
4961 case LTGT:
4962 return (known_results & CMP_EQ) ? const0_rtx : const_true_rtx;
4963
4964 case LT:
4965 case UNLT:
4966 return (known_results & CMP_LT) ? const_true_rtx : const0_rtx;
4967 case GE:
4968 case UNGE:
4969 return (known_results & CMP_LT) ? const0_rtx : const_true_rtx;
4970
4971 case GT:
4972 case UNGT:
4973 return (known_results & CMP_GT) ? const_true_rtx : const0_rtx;
4974 case LE:
4975 case UNLE:
4976 return (known_results & CMP_GT) ? const0_rtx : const_true_rtx;
4977
4978 case LTU:
4979 return (known_results & CMP_LTU) ? const_true_rtx : const0_rtx;
4980 case GEU:
4981 return (known_results & CMP_LTU) ? const0_rtx : const_true_rtx;
4982
4983 case GTU:
4984 return (known_results & CMP_GTU) ? const_true_rtx : const0_rtx;
4985 case LEU:
4986 return (known_results & CMP_GTU) ? const0_rtx : const_true_rtx;
4987
4988 case ORDERED:
4989 return const_true_rtx;
4990 case UNORDERED:
4991 return const0_rtx;
4992 default:
4993 gcc_unreachable ();
4994 }
4995}
4996
4997/* Check if the given comparison (done in the given MODE) is actually
4998 a tautology or a contradiction. If the mode is VOID_mode, the
4999 comparison is done in "infinite precision". If no simplification
5000 is possible, this function returns zero. Otherwise, it returns
5001 either const_true_rtx or const0_rtx. */
5002
5003rtx
5004simplify_const_relational_operation (enum rtx_code code,
5005 machine_mode mode,
5006 rtx op0, rtx op1)
5007{
5008 rtx tem;
5009 rtx trueop0;
5010 rtx trueop1;
5011
5012 gcc_assert (mode != VOIDmode
5013 || (GET_MODE (op0) == VOIDmode
5014 && GET_MODE (op1) == VOIDmode));
5015
5016 /* If op0 is a compare, extract the comparison arguments from it. */
5017 if (GET_CODE (op0) == COMPARE && op1 == const0_rtx)
5018 {
5019 op1 = XEXP (op0, 1);
5020 op0 = XEXP (op0, 0);
5021
5022 if (GET_MODE (op0) != VOIDmode)
5023 mode = GET_MODE (op0);
5024 else if (GET_MODE (op1) != VOIDmode)
5025 mode = GET_MODE (op1);
5026 else
5027 return 0;
5028 }
5029
5030 /* We can't simplify MODE_CC values since we don't know what the
5031 actual comparison is. */
5032 if (GET_MODE_CLASS (GET_MODE (op0)) == MODE_CC || CC0_P (op0))
5033 return 0;
5034
5035 /* Make sure the constant is second. */
5036 if (swap_commutative_operands_p (op0, op1))
5037 {
5038 std::swap (op0, op1);
5039 code = swap_condition (code);
5040 }
5041
5042 trueop0 = avoid_constant_pool_reference (op0);
5043 trueop1 = avoid_constant_pool_reference (op1);
5044
5045 /* For integer comparisons of A and B maybe we can simplify A - B and can
5046 then simplify a comparison of that with zero. If A and B are both either
5047 a register or a CONST_INT, this can't help; testing for these cases will
5048 prevent infinite recursion here and speed things up.
5049
5050 We can only do this for EQ and NE comparisons as otherwise we may
5051 lose or introduce overflow which we cannot disregard as undefined as
5052 we do not know the signedness of the operation on either the left or
5053 the right hand side of the comparison. */
5054
5055 if (INTEGRAL_MODE_P (mode) && trueop1 != const0_rtx
5056 && (code == EQ || code == NE)
5057 && ! ((REG_P (op0) || CONST_INT_P (trueop0))
5058 && (REG_P (op1) || CONST_INT_P (trueop1)))
5059 && 0 != (tem = simplify_binary_operation (MINUS, mode, op0, op1))
5060 /* We cannot do this if tem is a nonzero address. */
5061 && ! nonzero_address_p (tem))
5062 return simplify_const_relational_operation (signed_condition (code),
5063 mode, tem, const0_rtx);
5064
5065 if (! HONOR_NANS (mode) && code == ORDERED)
5066 return const_true_rtx;
5067
5068 if (! HONOR_NANS (mode) && code == UNORDERED)
5069 return const0_rtx;
5070
5071 /* For modes without NaNs, if the two operands are equal, we know the
5072 result except if they have side-effects. Even with NaNs we know
5073 the result of unordered comparisons and, if signaling NaNs are
5074 irrelevant, also the result of LT/GT/LTGT. */
5075 if ((! HONOR_NANS (trueop0)
5076 || code == UNEQ || code == UNLE || code == UNGE
5077 || ((code == LT || code == GT || code == LTGT)
5078 && ! HONOR_SNANS (trueop0)))
5079 && rtx_equal_p (trueop0, trueop1)
5080 && ! side_effects_p (trueop0))
5081 return comparison_result (code, CMP_EQ);
5082
5083 /* If the operands are floating-point constants, see if we can fold
5084 the result. */
5085 if (CONST_DOUBLE_AS_FLOAT_P (trueop0)
5086 && CONST_DOUBLE_AS_FLOAT_P (trueop1)
5087 && SCALAR_FLOAT_MODE_P (GET_MODE (trueop0)))
5088 {
5089 const REAL_VALUE_TYPE *d0 = CONST_DOUBLE_REAL_VALUE (trueop0);
5090 const REAL_VALUE_TYPE *d1 = CONST_DOUBLE_REAL_VALUE (trueop1);
5091
5092 /* Comparisons are unordered iff at least one of the values is NaN. */
5093 if (REAL_VALUE_ISNAN (*d0) || REAL_VALUE_ISNAN (*d1))
5094 switch (code)
5095 {
5096 case UNEQ:
5097 case UNLT:
5098 case UNGT:
5099 case UNLE:
5100 case UNGE:
5101 case NE:
5102 case UNORDERED:
5103 return const_true_rtx;
5104 case EQ:
5105 case LT:
5106 case GT:
5107 case LE:
5108 case GE:
5109 case LTGT:
5110 case ORDERED:
5111 return const0_rtx;
5112 default:
5113 return 0;
5114 }
5115
5116 return comparison_result (code,
5117 (real_equal (d0, d1) ? CMP_EQ :
5118 real_less (d0, d1) ? CMP_LT : CMP_GT));
5119 }
5120
5121 /* Otherwise, see if the operands are both integers. */
5122 if ((GET_MODE_CLASS (mode) == MODE_INT || mode == VOIDmode)
5123 && CONST_SCALAR_INT_P (trueop0) && CONST_SCALAR_INT_P (trueop1))
5124 {
5125 /* It would be nice if we really had a mode here. However, the
5126 largest int representable on the target is as good as
5127 infinite. */
5128 machine_mode cmode = (mode == VOIDmode) ? MAX_MODE_INT : mode;
5129 rtx_mode_t ptrueop0 = rtx_mode_t (trueop0, cmode);
5130 rtx_mode_t ptrueop1 = rtx_mode_t (trueop1, cmode);
5131
5132 if (wi::eq_p (ptrueop0, ptrueop1))
5133 return comparison_result (code, CMP_EQ);
5134 else
5135 {
5136 int cr = wi::lts_p (ptrueop0, ptrueop1) ? CMP_LT : CMP_GT;
5137 cr |= wi::ltu_p (ptrueop0, ptrueop1) ? CMP_LTU : CMP_GTU;
5138 return comparison_result (code, cr);
5139 }
5140 }
5141
5142 /* Optimize comparisons with upper and lower bounds. */
5143 if (HWI_COMPUTABLE_MODE_P (mode)
5144 && CONST_INT_P (trueop1)
5145 && !side_effects_p (trueop0))
5146 {
5147 int sign;
5148 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT nonzero = nonzero_bits (trueop0, mode);
5149 HOST_WIDE_INT val = INTVAL (trueop1);
5150 HOST_WIDE_INT mmin, mmax;
5151
5152 if (code == GEU
5153 || code == LEU
5154 || code == GTU
5155 || code == LTU)
5156 sign = 0;
5157 else
5158 sign = 1;
5159
5160 /* Get a reduced range if the sign bit is zero. */
5161 if (nonzero <= (GET_MODE_MASK (mode) >> 1))
5162 {
5163 mmin = 0;
5164 mmax = nonzero;
5165 }
5166 else
5167 {
5168 rtx mmin_rtx, mmax_rtx;
5169 get_mode_bounds (mode, sign, mode, &mmin_rtx, &mmax_rtx);
5170
5171 mmin = INTVAL (mmin_rtx);
5172 mmax = INTVAL (mmax_rtx);
5173 if (sign)
5174 {
5175 unsigned int sign_copies = num_sign_bit_copies (trueop0, mode);
5176
5177 mmin >>= (sign_copies - 1);
5178 mmax >>= (sign_copies - 1);
5179 }
5180 }
5181
5182 switch (code)
5183 {
5184 /* x >= y is always true for y <= mmin, always false for y > mmax. */
5185 case GEU:
5186 if ((unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT) val <= (unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT) mmin)
5187 return const_true_rtx;
5188 if ((unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT) val > (unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT) mmax)
5189 return const0_rtx;
5190 break;
5191 case GE:
5192 if (val <= mmin)
5193 return const_true_rtx;
5194 if (val > mmax)
5195 return const0_rtx;
5196 break;
5197
5198 /* x <= y is always true for y >= mmax, always false for y < mmin. */
5199 case LEU:
5200 if ((unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT) val >= (unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT) mmax)
5201 return const_true_rtx;
5202 if ((unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT) val < (unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT) mmin)
5203 return const0_rtx;
5204 break;
5205 case LE:
5206 if (val >= mmax)
5207 return const_true_rtx;
5208 if (val < mmin)
5209 return const0_rtx;
5210 break;
5211
5212 case EQ:
5213 /* x == y is always false for y out of range. */
5214 if (val < mmin || val > mmax)
5215 return const0_rtx;
5216 break;
5217
5218 /* x > y is always false for y >= mmax, always true for y < mmin. */
5219 case GTU:
5220 if ((unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT) val >= (unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT) mmax)
5221 return const0_rtx;
5222 if ((unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT) val < (unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT) mmin)
5223 return const_true_rtx;
5224 break;
5225 case GT:
5226 if (val >= mmax)
5227 return const0_rtx;
5228 if (val < mmin)
5229 return const_true_rtx;
5230 break;
5231
5232 /* x < y is always false for y <= mmin, always true for y > mmax. */
5233 case LTU:
5234 if ((unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT) val <= (unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT) mmin)
5235 return const0_rtx;
5236 if ((unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT) val > (unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT) mmax)
5237 return const_true_rtx;
5238 break;
5239 case LT:
5240 if (val <= mmin)
5241 return const0_rtx;
5242 if (val > mmax)
5243 return const_true_rtx;
5244 break;
5245
5246 case NE:
5247 /* x != y is always true for y out of range. */
5248 if (val < mmin || val > mmax)
5249 return const_true_rtx;
5250 break;
5251
5252 default:
5253 break;
5254 }
5255 }
5256
5257 /* Optimize integer comparisons with zero. */
5258 if (trueop1 == const0_rtx && !side_effects_p (trueop0))
5259 {
5260 /* Some addresses are known to be nonzero. We don't know
5261 their sign, but equality comparisons are known. */
5262 if (nonzero_address_p (trueop0))
5263 {
5264 if (code == EQ || code == LEU)
5265 return const0_rtx;
5266 if (code == NE || code == GTU)
5267 return const_true_rtx;
5268 }
5269
5270 /* See if the first operand is an IOR with a constant. If so, we
5271 may be able to determine the result of this comparison. */
5272 if (GET_CODE (op0) == IOR)
5273 {
5274 rtx inner_const = avoid_constant_pool_reference (XEXP (op0, 1));
5275 if (CONST_INT_P (inner_const) && inner_const != const0_rtx)
5276 {
5277 int sign_bitnum = GET_MODE_PRECISION (mode) - 1;
5278 int has_sign = (HOST_BITS_PER_WIDE_INT >= sign_bitnum
5279 && (UINTVAL (inner_const)
5280 & (HOST_WIDE_INT_1U
5281 << sign_bitnum)));
5282
5283 switch (code)
5284 {
5285 case EQ:
5286 case LEU:
5287 return const0_rtx;
5288 case NE:
5289 case GTU:
5290 return const_true_rtx;
5291 case LT:
5292 case LE:
5293 if (has_sign)
5294 return const_true_rtx;
5295 break;
5296 case GT:
5297 case GE:
5298 if (has_sign)
5299 return const0_rtx;
5300 break;
5301 default:
5302 break;
5303 }
5304 }
5305 }
5306 }
5307
5308 /* Optimize comparison of ABS with zero. */
5309 if (trueop1 == CONST0_RTX (mode) && !side_effects_p (trueop0)
5310 && (GET_CODE (trueop0) == ABS
5311 || (GET_CODE (trueop0) == FLOAT_EXTEND
5312 && GET_CODE (XEXP (trueop0, 0)) == ABS)))
5313 {
5314 switch (code)
5315 {
5316 case LT:
5317 /* Optimize abs(x) < 0.0. */
5318 if (!INTEGRAL_MODE_P (mode) && !HONOR_SNANS (mode))
5319 return const0_rtx;
5320 break;
5321
5322 case GE:
5323 /* Optimize abs(x) >= 0.0. */
5324 if (!INTEGRAL_MODE_P (mode) && !HONOR_NANS (mode))
5325 return const_true_rtx;
5326 break;
5327
5328 case UNGE:
5329 /* Optimize ! (abs(x) < 0.0). */
5330 return const_true_rtx;
5331
5332 default:
5333 break;
5334 }
5335 }
5336
5337 return 0;
5338}
5339
5340/* Recognize expressions of the form (X CMP 0) ? VAL : OP (X)
5341 where OP is CLZ or CTZ and VAL is the value from CLZ_DEFINED_VALUE_AT_ZERO
5342 or CTZ_DEFINED_VALUE_AT_ZERO respectively and return OP (X) if the expression
5343 can be simplified to that or NULL_RTX if not.
5344 Assume X is compared against zero with CMP_CODE and the true
5345 arm is TRUE_VAL and the false arm is FALSE_VAL. */
5346
5347static rtx
5348simplify_cond_clz_ctz (rtx x, rtx_code cmp_code, rtx true_val, rtx false_val)
5349{
5350 if (cmp_code != EQ && cmp_code != NE)
5351 return NULL_RTX;
5352
5353 /* Result on X == 0 and X !=0 respectively. */
5354 rtx on_zero, on_nonzero;
5355 if (cmp_code == EQ)
5356 {
5357 on_zero = true_val;
5358 on_nonzero = false_val;
5359 }
5360 else
5361 {
5362 on_zero = false_val;
5363 on_nonzero = true_val;
5364 }
5365
5366 rtx_code op_code = GET_CODE (on_nonzero);
5367 if ((op_code != CLZ && op_code != CTZ)
5368 || !rtx_equal_p (XEXP (on_nonzero, 0), x)
5369 || !CONST_INT_P (on_zero))
5370 return NULL_RTX;
5371
5372 HOST_WIDE_INT op_val;
5373 if (((op_code == CLZ
5374 && CLZ_DEFINED_VALUE_AT_ZERO (GET_MODE (on_nonzero), op_val))
5375 || (op_code == CTZ
5376 && CTZ_DEFINED_VALUE_AT_ZERO (GET_MODE (on_nonzero), op_val)))
5377 && op_val == INTVAL (on_zero))
5378 return on_nonzero;
5379
5380 return NULL_RTX;
5381}
5382
5383
5384/* Simplify CODE, an operation with result mode MODE and three operands,
5385 OP0, OP1, and OP2. OP0_MODE was the mode of OP0 before it became
5386 a constant. Return 0 if no simplifications is possible. */
5387
5388rtx
5389simplify_ternary_operation (enum rtx_code code, machine_mode mode,
5390 machine_mode op0_mode, rtx op0, rtx op1,
5391 rtx op2)
5392{
5393 unsigned int width = GET_MODE_PRECISION (mode);
5394 bool any_change = false;
5395 rtx tem, trueop2;
5396
5397 /* VOIDmode means "infinite" precision. */
5398 if (width == 0)
5399 width = HOST_BITS_PER_WIDE_INT;
5400
5401 switch (code)
5402 {
5403 case FMA:
5404 /* Simplify negations around the multiplication. */
5405 /* -a * -b + c => a * b + c. */
5406 if (GET_CODE (op0) == NEG)
5407 {
5408 tem = simplify_unary_operation (NEG, mode, op1, mode);
5409 if (tem)
5410 op1 = tem, op0 = XEXP (op0, 0), any_change = true;
5411 }
5412 else if (GET_CODE (op1) == NEG)
5413 {
5414 tem = simplify_unary_operation (NEG, mode, op0, mode);
5415 if (tem)
5416 op0 = tem, op1 = XEXP (op1, 0), any_change = true;
5417 }
5418
5419 /* Canonicalize the two multiplication operands. */
5420 /* a * -b + c => -b * a + c. */
5421 if (swap_commutative_operands_p (op0, op1))
5422 std::swap (op0, op1), any_change = true;
5423
5424 if (any_change)
5425 return gen_rtx_FMA (mode, op0, op1, op2);
5426 return NULL_RTX;
5427
5428 case SIGN_EXTRACT:
5429 case ZERO_EXTRACT:
5430 if (CONST_INT_P (op0)
5431 && CONST_INT_P (op1)
5432 && CONST_INT_P (op2)
5433 && ((unsigned) INTVAL (op1) + (unsigned) INTVAL (op2) <= width)
5434 && width <= (unsigned) HOST_BITS_PER_WIDE_INT)
5435 {
5436 /* Extracting a bit-field from a constant */
5437 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT val = UINTVAL (op0);
5438 HOST_WIDE_INT op1val = INTVAL (op1);
5439 HOST_WIDE_INT op2val = INTVAL (op2);
5440 if (BITS_BIG_ENDIAN)
5441 val >>= GET_MODE_PRECISION (op0_mode) - op2val - op1val;
5442 else
5443 val >>= op2val;
5444
5445 if (HOST_BITS_PER_WIDE_INT != op1val)
5446 {
5447 /* First zero-extend. */
5448 val &= (HOST_WIDE_INT_1U << op1val) - 1;
5449 /* If desired, propagate sign bit. */
5450 if (code == SIGN_EXTRACT
5451 && (val & (HOST_WIDE_INT_1U << (op1val - 1)))
5452 != 0)
5453 val |= ~ ((HOST_WIDE_INT_1U << op1val) - 1);
5454 }
5455
5456 return gen_int_mode (val, mode);
5457 }
5458 break;
5459
5460 case IF_THEN_ELSE:
5461 if (CONST_INT_P (op0))
5462 return op0 != const0_rtx ? op1 : op2;
5463
5464 /* Convert c ? a : a into "a". */
5465 if (rtx_equal_p (op1, op2) && ! side_effects_p (op0))
5466 return op1;
5467
5468 /* Convert a != b ? a : b into "a". */
5469 if (GET_CODE (op0) == NE
5470 && ! side_effects_p (op0)
5471 && ! HONOR_NANS (mode)
5472 && ! HONOR_SIGNED_ZEROS (mode)
5473 && ((rtx_equal_p (XEXP (op0, 0), op1)
5474 && rtx_equal_p (XEXP (op0, 1), op2))
5475 || (rtx_equal_p (XEXP (op0, 0), op2)
5476 && rtx_equal_p (XEXP (op0, 1), op1))))
5477 return op1;
5478
5479 /* Convert a == b ? a : b into "b". */
5480 if (GET_CODE (op0) == EQ
5481 && ! side_effects_p (op0)
5482 && ! HONOR_NANS (mode)
5483 && ! HONOR_SIGNED_ZEROS (mode)
5484 && ((rtx_equal_p (XEXP (op0, 0), op1)
5485 && rtx_equal_p (XEXP (op0, 1), op2))
5486 || (rtx_equal_p (XEXP (op0, 0), op2)
5487 && rtx_equal_p (XEXP (op0, 1), op1))))
5488 return op2;
5489
5490 /* Convert (!c) != {0,...,0} ? a : b into
5491 c != {0,...,0} ? b : a for vector modes. */
5492 if (VECTOR_MODE_P (GET_MODE (op1))
5493 && GET_CODE (op0) == NE
5494 && GET_CODE (XEXP (op0, 0)) == NOT
5495 && GET_CODE (XEXP (op0, 1)) == CONST_VECTOR)
5496 {
5497 rtx cv = XEXP (op0, 1);
5498 int nunits = CONST_VECTOR_NUNITS (cv);
5499 bool ok = true;
5500 for (int i = 0; i < nunits; ++i)
5501 if (CONST_VECTOR_ELT (cv, i) != const0_rtx)
5502 {
5503 ok = false;
5504 break;
5505 }
5506 if (ok)
5507 {
5508 rtx new_op0 = gen_rtx_NE (GET_MODE (op0),
5509 XEXP (XEXP (op0, 0), 0),
5510 XEXP (op0, 1));
5511 rtx retval = gen_rtx_IF_THEN_ELSE (mode, new_op0, op2, op1);
5512 return retval;
5513 }
5514 }
5515
5516 /* Convert x == 0 ? N : clz (x) into clz (x) when
5517 CLZ_DEFINED_VALUE_AT_ZERO is defined to N for the mode of x.
5518 Similarly for ctz (x). */
5519 if (COMPARISON_P (op0) && !side_effects_p (op0)
5520 && XEXP (op0, 1) == const0_rtx)
5521 {
5522 rtx simplified
5523 = simplify_cond_clz_ctz (XEXP (op0, 0), GET_CODE (op0),
5524 op1, op2);
5525 if (simplified)
5526 return simplified;
5527 }
5528
5529 if (COMPARISON_P (op0) && ! side_effects_p (op0))
5530 {
5531 machine_mode cmp_mode = (GET_MODE (XEXP (op0, 0)) == VOIDmode
5532 ? GET_MODE (XEXP (op0, 1))
5533 : GET_MODE (XEXP (op0, 0)));
5534 rtx temp;
5535
5536 /* Look for happy constants in op1 and op2. */
5537 if (CONST_INT_P (op1) && CONST_INT_P (op2))
5538 {
5539 HOST_WIDE_INT t = INTVAL (op1);
5540 HOST_WIDE_INT f = INTVAL (op2);
5541
5542 if (t == STORE_FLAG_VALUE && f == 0)
5543 code = GET_CODE (op0);
5544 else if (t == 0 && f == STORE_FLAG_VALUE)
5545 {
5546 enum rtx_code tmp;
5547 tmp = reversed_comparison_code (op0, NULL);
5548 if (tmp == UNKNOWN)
5549 break;
5550 code = tmp;
5551 }
5552 else
5553 break;
5554
5555 return simplify_gen_relational (code, mode, cmp_mode,
5556 XEXP (op0, 0), XEXP (op0, 1));
5557 }
5558
5559 if (cmp_mode == VOIDmode)
5560 cmp_mode = op0_mode;
5561 temp = simplify_relational_operation (GET_CODE (op0), op0_mode,
5562 cmp_mode, XEXP (op0, 0),
5563 XEXP (op0, 1));
5564
5565 /* See if any simplifications were possible. */
5566 if (temp)
5567 {
5568 if (CONST_INT_P (temp))
5569 return temp == const0_rtx ? op2 : op1;
5570 else if (temp)
5571 return gen_rtx_IF_THEN_ELSE (mode, temp, op1, op2);
5572 }
5573 }
5574 break;
5575
5576 case VEC_MERGE:
5577 gcc_assert (GET_MODE (op0) == mode);
5578 gcc_assert (GET_MODE (op1) == mode);
5579 gcc_assert (VECTOR_MODE_P (mode));
5580 trueop2 = avoid_constant_pool_reference (op2);
5581 if (CONST_INT_P (trueop2))
5582 {
5583 int elt_size = GET_MODE_UNIT_SIZE (mode);
5584 unsigned n_elts = (GET_MODE_SIZE (mode) / elt_size);
5585 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT sel = UINTVAL (trueop2);
5586 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT mask;
5587 if (n_elts == HOST_BITS_PER_WIDE_INT)
5588 mask = -1;
5589 else
5590 mask = (HOST_WIDE_INT_1U << n_elts) - 1;
5591
5592 if (!(sel & mask) && !side_effects_p (op0))
5593 return op1;
5594 if ((sel & mask) == mask && !side_effects_p (op1))
5595 return op0;
5596
5597 rtx trueop0 = avoid_constant_pool_reference (op0);
5598 rtx trueop1 = avoid_constant_pool_reference (op1);
5599 if (GET_CODE (trueop0) == CONST_VECTOR
5600 && GET_CODE (trueop1) == CONST_VECTOR)
5601 {
5602 rtvec v = rtvec_alloc (n_elts);
5603 unsigned int i;
5604
5605 for (i = 0; i < n_elts; i++)
5606 RTVEC_ELT (v, i) = ((sel & (HOST_WIDE_INT_1U << i))
5607 ? CONST_VECTOR_ELT (trueop0, i)
5608 : CONST_VECTOR_ELT (trueop1, i));
5609 return gen_rtx_CONST_VECTOR (mode, v);
5610 }
5611
5612 /* Replace (vec_merge (vec_merge a b m) c n) with (vec_merge b c n)
5613 if no element from a appears in the result. */
5614 if (GET_CODE (op0) == VEC_MERGE)
5615 {
5616 tem = avoid_constant_pool_reference (XEXP (op0, 2));
5617 if (CONST_INT_P (tem))
5618 {
5619 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT sel0 = UINTVAL (tem);
5620 if (!(sel & sel0 & mask) && !side_effects_p (XEXP (op0, 0)))
5621 return simplify_gen_ternary (code, mode, mode,
5622 XEXP (op0, 1), op1, op2);
5623 if (!(sel & ~sel0 & mask) && !side_effects_p (XEXP (op0, 1)))
5624 return simplify_gen_ternary (code, mode, mode,
5625 XEXP (op0, 0), op1, op2);
5626 }
5627 }
5628 if (GET_CODE (op1) == VEC_MERGE)
5629 {
5630 tem = avoid_constant_pool_reference (XEXP (op1, 2));
5631 if (CONST_INT_P (tem))
5632 {
5633 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT sel1 = UINTVAL (tem);
5634 if (!(~sel & sel1 & mask) && !side_effects_p (XEXP (op1, 0)))
5635 return simplify_gen_ternary (code, mode, mode,
5636 op0, XEXP (op1, 1), op2);
5637 if (!(~sel & ~sel1 & mask) && !side_effects_p (XEXP (op1, 1)))
5638 return simplify_gen_ternary (code, mode, mode,
5639 op0, XEXP (op1, 0), op2);
5640 }
5641 }
5642
5643 /* Replace (vec_merge (vec_duplicate (vec_select a parallel (i))) a 1 << i)
5644 with a. */
5645 if (GET_CODE (op0) == VEC_DUPLICATE
5646 && GET_CODE (XEXP (op0, 0)) == VEC_SELECT
5647 && GET_CODE (XEXP (XEXP (op0, 0), 1)) == PARALLEL
5648 && mode_nunits[GET_MODE (XEXP (op0, 0))] == 1)
5649 {
5650 tem = XVECEXP ((XEXP (XEXP (op0, 0), 1)), 0, 0);
5651 if (CONST_INT_P (tem) && CONST_INT_P (op2))
5652 {
5653 if (XEXP (XEXP (op0, 0), 0) == op1
5654 && UINTVAL (op2) == HOST_WIDE_INT_1U << UINTVAL (tem))
5655 return op1;
5656 }
5657 }
5658 }
5659
5660 if (rtx_equal_p (op0, op1)
5661 && !side_effects_p (op2) && !side_effects_p (op1))
5662 return op0;
5663
5664 break;
5665
5666 default:
5667 gcc_unreachable ();
5668 }
5669
5670 return 0;
5671}
5672
5673/* Evaluate a SUBREG of a CONST_INT or CONST_WIDE_INT or CONST_DOUBLE
5674 or CONST_FIXED or CONST_VECTOR, returning another CONST_INT or
5675 CONST_WIDE_INT or CONST_DOUBLE or CONST_FIXED or CONST_VECTOR.
5676
5677 Works by unpacking OP into a collection of 8-bit values
5678 represented as a little-endian array of 'unsigned char', selecting by BYTE,
5679 and then repacking them again for OUTERMODE. */
5680
5681static rtx
5682simplify_immed_subreg (machine_mode outermode, rtx op,
5683 machine_mode innermode, unsigned int byte)
5684{
5685 enum {
5686 value_bit = 8,
5687 value_mask = (1 << value_bit) - 1
5688 };
5689 unsigned char value[MAX_BITSIZE_MODE_ANY_MODE / value_bit];
5690 int value_start;
5691 int i;
5692 int elem;
5693
5694 int num_elem;
5695 rtx * elems;
5696 int elem_bitsize;
5697 rtx result_s = NULL;
5698 rtvec result_v = NULL;
5699 enum mode_class outer_class;
5700 machine_mode outer_submode;
5701 int max_bitsize;
5702
5703 /* Some ports misuse CCmode. */
5704 if (GET_MODE_CLASS (outermode) == MODE_CC && CONST_INT_P (op))
5705 return op;
5706
5707 /* We have no way to represent a complex constant at the rtl level. */
5708 if (COMPLEX_MODE_P (outermode))
5709 return NULL_RTX;
5710
5711 /* We support any size mode. */
5712 max_bitsize = MAX (GET_MODE_BITSIZE (outermode),
5713 GET_MODE_BITSIZE (innermode));
5714
5715 /* Unpack the value. */
5716
5717 if (GET_CODE (op) == CONST_VECTOR)
5718 {
5719 num_elem = CONST_VECTOR_NUNITS (op);
5720 elems = &CONST_VECTOR_ELT (op, 0);
5721 elem_bitsize = GET_MODE_UNIT_BITSIZE (innermode);
5722 }
5723 else
5724 {
5725 num_elem = 1;
5726 elems = &op;
5727 elem_bitsize = max_bitsize;
5728 }
5729 /* If this asserts, it is too complicated; reducing value_bit may help. */
5730 gcc_assert (BITS_PER_UNIT % value_bit == 0);
5731 /* I don't know how to handle endianness of sub-units. */
5732 gcc_assert (elem_bitsize % BITS_PER_UNIT == 0);
5733
5734 for (elem = 0; elem < num_elem; elem++)
5735 {
5736 unsigned char * vp;
5737 rtx el = elems[elem];
5738
5739 /* Vectors are kept in target memory order. (This is probably
5740 a mistake.) */
5741 {
5742 unsigned byte = (elem * elem_bitsize) / BITS_PER_UNIT;
5743 unsigned ibyte = (((num_elem - 1 - elem) * elem_bitsize)
5744 / BITS_PER_UNIT);
5745 unsigned word_byte = WORDS_BIG_ENDIAN ? ibyte : byte;
5746 unsigned subword_byte = BYTES_BIG_ENDIAN ? ibyte : byte;
5747 unsigned bytele = (subword_byte % UNITS_PER_WORD
5748 + (word_byte / UNITS_PER_WORD) * UNITS_PER_WORD);
5749 vp = value + (bytele * BITS_PER_UNIT) / value_bit;
5750 }
5751
5752 switch (GET_CODE (el))
5753 {
5754 case CONST_INT:
5755 for (i = 0;
5756 i < HOST_BITS_PER_WIDE_INT && i < elem_bitsize;
5757 i += value_bit)
5758 *vp++ = INTVAL (el) >> i;
5759 /* CONST_INTs are always logically sign-extended. */
5760 for (; i < elem_bitsize; i += value_bit)
5761 *vp++ = INTVAL (el) < 0 ? -1 : 0;
5762 break;
5763
5764 case CONST_WIDE_INT:
5765 {
5766 rtx_mode_t val = rtx_mode_t (el, innermode);
5767 unsigned char extend = wi::sign_mask (val);
5768 int prec = wi::get_precision (val);
5769
5770 for (i = 0; i < prec && i < elem_bitsize; i += value_bit)
5771 *vp++ = wi::extract_uhwi (val, i, value_bit);
5772 for (; i < elem_bitsize; i += value_bit)
5773 *vp++ = extend;
5774 }
5775 break;
5776
5777 case CONST_DOUBLE:
5778 if (TARGET_SUPPORTS_WIDE_INT == 0 && GET_MODE (el) == VOIDmode)
5779 {
5780 unsigned char extend = 0;
5781 /* If this triggers, someone should have generated a
5782 CONST_INT instead. */
5783 gcc_assert (elem_bitsize > HOST_BITS_PER_WIDE_INT);
5784
5785 for (i = 0; i < HOST_BITS_PER_WIDE_INT; i += value_bit)
5786 *vp++ = CONST_DOUBLE_LOW (el) >> i;
5787 while (i < HOST_BITS_PER_DOUBLE_INT && i < elem_bitsize)
5788 {
5789 *vp++
5790 = CONST_DOUBLE_HIGH (el) >> (i - HOST_BITS_PER_WIDE_INT);
5791 i += value_bit;
5792 }
5793
5794 if (CONST_DOUBLE_HIGH (el) >> (HOST_BITS_PER_WIDE_INT - 1))
5795 extend = -1;
5796 for (; i < elem_bitsize; i += value_bit)
5797 *vp++ = extend;
5798 }
5799 else
5800 {
5801 /* This is big enough for anything on the platform. */
5802 long tmp[MAX_BITSIZE_MODE_ANY_MODE / 32];
5803 int bitsize = GET_MODE_BITSIZE (GET_MODE (el));
5804
5805 gcc_assert (SCALAR_FLOAT_MODE_P (GET_MODE (el)));
5806 gcc_assert (bitsize <= elem_bitsize);
5807 gcc_assert (bitsize % value_bit == 0);
5808
5809 real_to_target (tmp, CONST_DOUBLE_REAL_VALUE (el),
5810 GET_MODE (el));
5811
5812 /* real_to_target produces its result in words affected by
5813 FLOAT_WORDS_BIG_ENDIAN. However, we ignore this,
5814 and use WORDS_BIG_ENDIAN instead; see the documentation
5815 of SUBREG in rtl.texi. */
5816 for (i = 0; i < bitsize; i += value_bit)
5817 {
5818 int ibase;
5819 if (WORDS_BIG_ENDIAN)
5820 ibase = bitsize - 1 - i;
5821 else
5822 ibase = i;
5823 *vp++ = tmp[ibase / 32] >> i % 32;
5824 }
5825
5826 /* It shouldn't matter what's done here, so fill it with
5827 zero. */
5828 for (; i < elem_bitsize; i += value_bit)
5829 *vp++ = 0;
5830 }
5831 break;
5832
5833 case CONST_FIXED:
5834 if (elem_bitsize <= HOST_BITS_PER_WIDE_INT)
5835 {
5836 for (i = 0; i < elem_bitsize; i += value_bit)
5837 *vp++ = CONST_FIXED_VALUE_LOW (el) >> i;
5838 }
5839 else
5840 {
5841 for (i = 0; i < HOST_BITS_PER_WIDE_INT; i += value_bit)
5842 *vp++ = CONST_FIXED_VALUE_LOW (el) >> i;
5843 for (; i < HOST_BITS_PER_DOUBLE_INT && i < elem_bitsize;
5844 i += value_bit)
5845 *vp++ = CONST_FIXED_VALUE_HIGH (el)
5846 >> (i - HOST_BITS_PER_WIDE_INT);
5847 for (; i < elem_bitsize; i += value_bit)
5848 *vp++ = 0;
5849 }
5850 break;
5851
5852 default:
5853 gcc_unreachable ();
5854 }
5855 }
5856
5857 /* Now, pick the right byte to start with. */
5858 /* Renumber BYTE so that the least-significant byte is byte 0. A special
5859 case is paradoxical SUBREGs, which shouldn't be adjusted since they
5860 will already have offset 0. */
5861 if (GET_MODE_SIZE (innermode) >= GET_MODE_SIZE (outermode))
5862 {
5863 unsigned ibyte = (GET_MODE_SIZE (innermode) - GET_MODE_SIZE (outermode)
5864 - byte);
5865 unsigned word_byte = WORDS_BIG_ENDIAN ? ibyte : byte;
5866 unsigned subword_byte = BYTES_BIG_ENDIAN ? ibyte : byte;
5867 byte = (subword_byte % UNITS_PER_WORD
5868 + (word_byte / UNITS_PER_WORD) * UNITS_PER_WORD);
5869 }
5870
5871 /* BYTE should still be inside OP. (Note that BYTE is unsigned,
5872 so if it's become negative it will instead be very large.) */
5873 gcc_assert (byte < GET_MODE_SIZE (innermode));
5874
5875 /* Convert from bytes to chunks of size value_bit. */
5876 value_start = byte * (BITS_PER_UNIT / value_bit);
5877
5878 /* Re-pack the value. */
5879 num_elem = GET_MODE_NUNITS (outermode);
5880
5881 if (VECTOR_MODE_P (outermode))
5882 {
5883 result_v = rtvec_alloc (num_elem);
5884 elems = &RTVEC_ELT (result_v, 0);
5885 }
5886 else
5887 elems = &result_s;
5888
5889 outer_submode = GET_MODE_INNER (outermode);
5890 outer_class = GET_MODE_CLASS (outer_submode);
5891 elem_bitsize = GET_MODE_BITSIZE (outer_submode);
5892
5893 gcc_assert (elem_bitsize % value_bit == 0);
5894 gcc_assert (elem_bitsize + value_start * value_bit <= max_bitsize);
5895
5896 for (elem = 0; elem < num_elem; elem++)
5897 {
5898 unsigned char *vp;
5899
5900 /* Vectors are stored in target memory order. (This is probably
5901 a mistake.) */
5902 {
5903 unsigned byte = (elem * elem_bitsize) / BITS_PER_UNIT;
5904 unsigned ibyte = (((num_elem - 1 - elem) * elem_bitsize)
5905 / BITS_PER_UNIT);
5906 unsigned word_byte = WORDS_BIG_ENDIAN ? ibyte : byte;
5907 unsigned subword_byte = BYTES_BIG_ENDIAN ? ibyte : byte;
5908 unsigned bytele = (subword_byte % UNITS_PER_WORD
5909 + (word_byte / UNITS_PER_WORD) * UNITS_PER_WORD);
5910 vp = value + value_start + (bytele * BITS_PER_UNIT) / value_bit;
5911 }
5912
5913 switch (outer_class)
5914 {
5915 case MODE_INT:
5916 case MODE_PARTIAL_INT:
5917 {
5918 int u;
5919 int base = 0;
5920 int units
5921 = (GET_MODE_BITSIZE (outer_submode) + HOST_BITS_PER_WIDE_INT - 1)
5922 / HOST_BITS_PER_WIDE_INT;
5923 HOST_WIDE_INT tmp[MAX_BITSIZE_MODE_ANY_INT / HOST_BITS_PER_WIDE_INT];
5924 wide_int r;
5925
5926 if (GET_MODE_PRECISION (outer_submode) > MAX_BITSIZE_MODE_ANY_INT)
5927 return NULL_RTX;
5928 for (u = 0; u < units; u++)
5929 {
5930 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT buf = 0;
5931 for (i = 0;
5932 i < HOST_BITS_PER_WIDE_INT && base + i < elem_bitsize;
5933 i += value_bit)
5934 buf |= (unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT)(*vp++ & value_mask) << i;
5935
5936 tmp[u] = buf;
5937 base += HOST_BITS_PER_WIDE_INT;
5938 }
5939 r = wide_int::from_array (tmp, units,
5940 GET_MODE_PRECISION (outer_submode));
5941#if TARGET_SUPPORTS_WIDE_INT == 0
5942 /* Make sure r will fit into CONST_INT or CONST_DOUBLE. */
5943 if (wi::min_precision (r, SIGNED) > HOST_BITS_PER_DOUBLE_INT)
5944 return NULL_RTX;
5945#endif
5946 elems[elem] = immed_wide_int_const (r, outer_submode);
5947 }
5948 break;
5949
5950 case MODE_FLOAT:
5951 case MODE_DECIMAL_FLOAT:
5952 {
5953 REAL_VALUE_TYPE r;
5954 long tmp[MAX_BITSIZE_MODE_ANY_MODE / 32] = { 0 };
5955
5956 /* real_from_target wants its input in words affected by
5957 FLOAT_WORDS_BIG_ENDIAN. However, we ignore this,
5958 and use WORDS_BIG_ENDIAN instead; see the documentation
5959 of SUBREG in rtl.texi. */
5960 for (i = 0; i < elem_bitsize; i += value_bit)
5961 {
5962 int ibase;
5963 if (WORDS_BIG_ENDIAN)
5964 ibase = elem_bitsize - 1 - i;
5965 else
5966 ibase = i;
5967 tmp[ibase / 32] |= (*vp++ & value_mask) << i % 32;
5968 }
5969
5970 real_from_target (&r, tmp, outer_submode);
5971 elems[elem] = const_double_from_real_value (r, outer_submode);
5972 }
5973 break;
5974
5975 case MODE_FRACT:
5976 case MODE_UFRACT:
5977 case MODE_ACCUM:
5978 case MODE_UACCUM:
5979 {
5980 FIXED_VALUE_TYPE f;
5981 f.data.low = 0;
5982 f.data.high = 0;
5983 f.mode = outer_submode;
5984
5985 for (i = 0;
5986 i < HOST_BITS_PER_WIDE_INT && i < elem_bitsize;
5987 i += value_bit)
5988 f.data.low |= (unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT)(*vp++ & value_mask) << i;
5989 for (; i < elem_bitsize; i += value_bit)
5990 f.data.high |= ((unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT)(*vp++ & value_mask)
5991 << (i - HOST_BITS_PER_WIDE_INT));
5992
5993 elems[elem] = CONST_FIXED_FROM_FIXED_VALUE (f, outer_submode);
5994 }
5995 break;
5996
5997 default:
5998 gcc_unreachable ();
5999 }
6000 }
6001 if (VECTOR_MODE_P (outermode))
6002 return gen_rtx_CONST_VECTOR (outermode, result_v);
6003 else
6004 return result_s;
6005}

6007/* Simplify SUBREG:OUTERMODE(OP:INNERMODE, BYTE)
6008 Return 0 if no simplifications are possible. */
6009rtx
6010simplify_subreg (machine_mode outermode, rtx op,
6011 machine_mode innermode, unsigned int byte)
6012{
6013 /* Little bit of sanity checking. */
6014 gcc_assert (innermode != VOIDmode);
6015 gcc_assert (outermode != VOIDmode);
6016 gcc_assert (innermode != BLKmode);
6017 gcc_assert (outermode != BLKmode);
6018
6019 gcc_assert (GET_MODE (op) == innermode
6020 || GET_MODE (op) == VOIDmode);
6021
6022 if ((byte % GET_MODE_SIZE (outermode)) != 0)
6023 return NULL_RTX;
6024
6025 if (byte >= GET_MODE_SIZE (innermode))
6026 return NULL_RTX;
6027
6028 if (outermode == innermode && !byte)
6029 return op;
6030
6031 if (CONST_SCALAR_INT_P (op)
6032 || CONST_DOUBLE_AS_FLOAT_P (op)
6033 || GET_CODE (op) == CONST_FIXED
6034 || GET_CODE (op) == CONST_VECTOR)
6035 return simplify_immed_subreg (outermode, op, innermode, byte);
6036
6037 /* Changing mode twice with SUBREG => just change it once,
6038 or not at all if changing back op starting mode. */
6039 if (GET_CODE (op) == SUBREG)
6040 {
6041 machine_mode innermostmode = GET_MODE (SUBREG_REG (op));
6042 int final_offset = byte + SUBREG_BYTE (op);
6043 rtx newx;
6044
6045 if (outermode == innermostmode
6046 && byte == 0 && SUBREG_BYTE (op) == 0)
6047 return SUBREG_REG (op);
6048
6049 /* The SUBREG_BYTE represents offset, as if the value were stored
6050 in memory. Irritating exception is paradoxical subreg, where
6051 we define SUBREG_BYTE to be 0. On big endian machines, this
6052 value should be negative. For a moment, undo this exception. */
6053 if (byte == 0 && GET_MODE_SIZE (innermode) < GET_MODE_SIZE (outermode))
6054 {
6055 int difference = (GET_MODE_SIZE (innermode) - GET_MODE_SIZE (outermode));
6056 if (WORDS_BIG_ENDIAN)
6057 final_offset += (difference / UNITS_PER_WORD) * UNITS_PER_WORD;
6058 if (BYTES_BIG_ENDIAN)
6059 final_offset += difference % UNITS_PER_WORD;
6060 }
6061 if (SUBREG_BYTE (op) == 0
6062 && GET_MODE_SIZE (innermostmode) < GET_MODE_SIZE (innermode))
6063 {
6064 int difference = (GET_MODE_SIZE (innermostmode) - GET_MODE_SIZE (innermode));
6065 if (WORDS_BIG_ENDIAN)
6066 final_offset += (difference / UNITS_PER_WORD) * UNITS_PER_WORD;
6067 if (BYTES_BIG_ENDIAN)
6068 final_offset += difference % UNITS_PER_WORD;
6069 }
6070
6071 /* See whether resulting subreg will be paradoxical. */
6072 if (GET_MODE_SIZE (innermostmode) > GET_MODE_SIZE (outermode))
6073 {
6074 /* In nonparadoxical subregs we can't handle negative offsets. */
6075 if (final_offset < 0)
6076 return NULL_RTX;
6077 /* Bail out in case resulting subreg would be incorrect. */
6078 if (final_offset % GET_MODE_SIZE (outermode)
6079 || (unsigned) final_offset >= GET_MODE_SIZE (innermostmode))
6080 return NULL_RTX;
6081 }
6082 else
6083 {
6084 int offset = 0;
6085 int difference = (GET_MODE_SIZE (innermostmode) - GET_MODE_SIZE (outermode));
6086
6087 /* In paradoxical subreg, see if we are still looking on lower part.
6088 If so, our SUBREG_BYTE will be 0. */
6089 if (WORDS_BIG_ENDIAN)
6090 offset += (difference / UNITS_PER_WORD) * UNITS_PER_WORD;
6091 if (BYTES_BIG_ENDIAN)
6092 offset += difference % UNITS_PER_WORD;
6093 if (offset == final_offset)
6094 final_offset = 0;
6095 else
6096 return NULL_RTX;
6097 }
6098
6099 /* Recurse for further possible simplifications. */
6100 newx = simplify_subreg (outermode, SUBREG_REG (op), innermostmode,
6101 final_offset);
6102 if (newx)
6103 return newx;
6104 if (validate_subreg (outermode, innermostmode,
6105 SUBREG_REG (op), final_offset))
6106 {
6107 newx = gen_rtx_SUBREG (outermode, SUBREG_REG (op), final_offset);
6108 if (SUBREG_PROMOTED_VAR_P (op)
6109 && SUBREG_PROMOTED_SIGN (op) >= 0
6110 && GET_MODE_CLASS (outermode) == MODE_INT
6111 && IN_RANGE (GET_MODE_SIZE (outermode),
6112 GET_MODE_SIZE (innermode),
6113 GET_MODE_SIZE (innermostmode))
6114 && subreg_lowpart_p (newx))
6115 {
6116 SUBREG_PROMOTED_VAR_P (newx) = 1;
6117 SUBREG_PROMOTED_SET (newx, SUBREG_PROMOTED_GET (op));
6118 }
6119 return newx;
6120 }
6121 return NULL_RTX;
6122 }
6123
6124 /* SUBREG of a hard register => just change the register number
6125 and/or mode. If the hard register is not valid in that mode,
6126 suppress this simplification. If the hard register is the stack,
6127 frame, or argument pointer, leave this as a SUBREG. */
6128
6129 if (REG_P (op) && HARD_REGISTER_P (op))
6130 {
6131 unsigned int regno, final_regno;
6132
6133 regno = REGNO (op);
6134 final_regno = simplify_subreg_regno (regno, innermode, byte, outermode);
6135 if (HARD_REGISTER_NUM_P (final_regno))
6136 {
6137 rtx x;
6138 int final_offset = byte;
6139
6140 /* Adjust offset for paradoxical subregs. */
6141 if (byte == 0
6142 && GET_MODE_SIZE (innermode) < GET_MODE_SIZE (outermode))
6143 {
6144 int difference = (GET_MODE_SIZE (innermode)
6145 - GET_MODE_SIZE (outermode));
6146 if (WORDS_BIG_ENDIAN)
6147 final_offset += (difference / UNITS_PER_WORD) * UNITS_PER_WORD;
6148 if (BYTES_BIG_ENDIAN)
6149 final_offset += difference % UNITS_PER_WORD;
6150 }
6151
6152 x = gen_rtx_REG_offset (op, outermode, final_regno, final_offset);
6153
6154 /* Propagate original regno. We don't have any way to specify
6155 the offset inside original regno, so do so only for lowpart.
6156 The information is used only by alias analysis that can not
6157 grog partial register anyway. */
6158
6159 if (subreg_lowpart_offset (outermode, innermode) == byte)
6160 ORIGINAL_REGNO (x) = ORIGINAL_REGNO (op);
6161 return x;
6162 }
6163 }
6164
6165 /* If we have a SUBREG of a register that we are replacing and we are
6166 replacing it with a MEM, make a new MEM and try replacing the
6167 SUBREG with it. Don't do this if the MEM has a mode-dependent address
6168 or if we would be widening it. */
6169
6170 if (MEM_P (op)
6171 && ! mode_dependent_address_p (XEXP (op, 0), MEM_ADDR_SPACE (op))
6172 /* Allow splitting of volatile memory references in case we don't
6173 have instruction to move the whole thing. */
6174 && (! MEM_VOLATILE_P (op)
6175 || ! have_insn_for (SET, innermode))
6176 && GET_MODE_SIZE (outermode) <= GET_MODE_SIZE (GET_MODE (op)))
6177 return adjust_address_nv (op, outermode, byte);
6178
6179 /* Handle complex or vector values represented as CONCAT or VEC_CONCAT
6180 of two parts. */
6181 if (GET_CODE (op) == CONCAT
6182 || GET_CODE (op) == VEC_CONCAT)
6183 {
6184 unsigned int part_size, final_offset;
6185 rtx part, res;
6186
6187 enum machine_mode part_mode = GET_MODE (XEXP (op, 0));
6188 if (part_mode == VOIDmode)
6189 part_mode = GET_MODE_INNER (GET_MODE (op));
6190 part_size = GET_MODE_SIZE (part_mode);
6191 if (byte < part_size)
6192 {
6193 part = XEXP (op, 0);
6194 final_offset = byte;
6195 }
6196 else
6197 {
6198 part = XEXP (op, 1);
6199 final_offset = byte - part_size;
6200 }
6201
6202 if (final_offset + GET_MODE_SIZE (outermode) > part_size)
6203 return NULL_RTX;
6204
6205 part_mode = GET_MODE (part);
6206 if (part_mode == VOIDmode)
6207 part_mode = GET_MODE_INNER (GET_MODE (op));
6208 res = simplify_subreg (outermode, part, part_mode, final_offset);
6209 if (res)
6210 return res;
6211 if (validate_subreg (outermode, part_mode, part, final_offset))
6212 return gen_rtx_SUBREG (outermode, part, final_offset);
6213 return NULL_RTX;
6214 }
6215
6216 /* A SUBREG resulting from a zero extension may fold to zero if
6217 it extracts higher bits that the ZERO_EXTEND's source bits. */
6218 if (GET_CODE (op) == ZERO_EXTEND && SCALAR_INT_MODE_P (innermode))
6219 {
6220 unsigned int bitpos = subreg_lsb_1 (outermode, innermode, byte);
6221 if (bitpos >= GET_MODE_PRECISION (GET_MODE (XEXP (op, 0))))
6222 return CONST0_RTX (outermode);
6223 }
6224
6225 if (SCALAR_INT_MODE_P (outermode)
6226 && SCALAR_INT_MODE_P (innermode)
6227 && GET_MODE_PRECISION (outermode) < GET_MODE_PRECISION (innermode)
6228 && byte == subreg_lowpart_offset (outermode, innermode))
6229 {
6230 rtx tem = simplify_truncation (outermode, op, innermode);
6231 if (tem)
6232 return tem;
6233 }
6234
6235 return NULL_RTX;
6236}
6237
6238/* Make a SUBREG operation or equivalent if it folds. */
6239
6240rtx
6241simplify_gen_subreg (machine_mode outermode, rtx op,
6242 machine_mode innermode, unsigned int byte)
6243{
6244 rtx newx;
6245
6246 newx = simplify_subreg (outermode, op, innermode, byte);
6247 if (newx)
6248 return newx;
6249
6250 if (GET_CODE (op) == SUBREG
6251 || GET_CODE (op) == CONCAT
6252 || GET_MODE (op) == VOIDmode)
6253 return NULL_RTX;
6254
6255 if (validate_subreg (outermode, innermode, op, byte))
6256 return gen_rtx_SUBREG (outermode, op, byte);
6257
6258 return NULL_RTX;
6259}

6261/* Generates a subreg to get the least significant part of EXPR (in mode
6262 INNER_MODE) to OUTER_MODE. */
6263
6264rtx
6265lowpart_subreg (machine_mode outer_mode, rtx expr,
6266 machine_mode inner_mode)
6267{
6268 return simplify_gen_subreg (outer_mode, expr, inner_mode,
6269 subreg_lowpart_offset (outer_mode, inner_mode));
6270}
6271
6272/* Simplify X, an rtx expression.
6273
6274 Return the simplified expression or NULL if no simplifications
6275 were possible.
6276
6277 This is the preferred entry point into the simplification routines;
6278 however, we still allow passes to call the more specific routines.
6279
6280 Right now GCC has three (yes, three) major bodies of RTL simplification
6281 code that need to be unified.
6282
6283 1. fold_rtx in cse.c. This code uses various CSE specific
6284 information to aid in RTL simplification.
6285
6286 2. simplify_rtx in combine.c. Similar to fold_rtx, except that
6287 it uses combine specific information to aid in RTL
6288 simplification.
6289
6290 3. The routines in this file.
6291
6292
6293 Long term we want to only have one body of simplification code; to
6294 get to that state I recommend the following steps:
6295
6296 1. Pour over fold_rtx & simplify_rtx and move any simplifications
6297 which are not pass dependent state into these routines.
6298
6299 2. As code is moved by #1, change fold_rtx & simplify_rtx to
6300 use this routine whenever possible.
6301
6302 3. Allow for pass dependent state to be provided to these
6303 routines and add simplifications based on the pass dependent
6304 state. Remove code from cse.c & combine.c that becomes
6305 redundant/dead.
6306
6307 It will take time, but ultimately the compiler will be easier to
6308 maintain and improve. It's totally silly that when we add a
6309 simplification that it needs to be added to 4 places (3 for RTL
6310 simplification and 1 for tree simplification. */
6311
6312rtx
6313simplify_rtx (const_rtx x)
6314{
6315 const enum rtx_code code = GET_CODE (x);
6316 const machine_mode mode = GET_MODE (x);
6317
6318 switch (GET_RTX_CLASS (code))
6319 {
6320 case RTX_UNARY:
6321 return simplify_unary_operation (code, mode,
6322 XEXP (x, 0), GET_MODE (XEXP (x, 0)));
6323 case RTX_COMM_ARITH:
6324 if (swap_commutative_operands_p (XEXP (x, 0), XEXP (x, 1)))
6325 return simplify_gen_binary (code, mode, XEXP (x, 1), XEXP (x, 0));
6326
6327 /* Fall through. */
6328
6329 case RTX_BIN_ARITH:
6330 return simplify_binary_operation (code, mode, XEXP (x, 0), XEXP (x, 1));
6331
6332 case RTX_TERNARY:
6333 case RTX_BITFIELD_OPS:
6334 return simplify_ternary_operation (code, mode, GET_MODE (XEXP (x, 0)),
6335 XEXP (x, 0), XEXP (x, 1),
6336 XEXP (x, 2));
6337
6338 case RTX_COMPARE:
6339 case RTX_COMM_COMPARE:
6340 return simplify_relational_operation (code, mode,
6341 ((GET_MODE (XEXP (x, 0))
6342 != VOIDmode)
6343 ? GET_MODE (XEXP (x, 0))
6344 : GET_MODE (XEXP (x, 1))),
6345 XEXP (x, 0),
6346 XEXP (x, 1));
6347
6348 case RTX_EXTRA:
6349 if (code == SUBREG)
6350 return simplify_subreg (mode, SUBREG_REG (x),
6351 GET_MODE (SUBREG_REG (x)),
6352 SUBREG_BYTE (x));
6353 break;
6354
6355 case RTX_OBJ:
6356 if (code == LO_SUM)
6357 {
6358 /* Convert (lo_sum (high FOO) FOO) to FOO. */
6359 if (GET_CODE (XEXP (x, 0)) == HIGH
6360 && rtx_equal_p (XEXP (XEXP (x, 0), 0), XEXP (x, 1)))
6361 return XEXP (x, 1);
6362 }
6363 break;
6364
6365 default:
6366 break;
6367 }
6368 return NULL;
6369}
